Color Pix is a thoughtfully designed Chrome extension created to simplify the way users interact with colors on the web. Developed as a modern color picker and palette management tool, it allows users to identify, capture, and organize colors directly from any webpage with precision and ease.

Built as a first independent browser extension project, Color Pix combines functionality with simplicity, offering a smooth experience for developers, designers, digital artists, and creative enthusiasts. Beyond basic color detection, the extension provides a dedicated palette system capable of storing up to 36 different shades, enabling users to build, manage, and revisit their favorite color combinations effortlessly.

The extension supports efficient color workflow management by helping users create visually consistent palettes for web design, branding, UI/UX development, and creative projects. Its lightweight architecture and intuitive interface make it accessible for both beginners and professionals looking for a reliable everyday color utility.

Color Pix represents a practical blend of creativity and usability — transforming everyday browsing into an interactive color exploration experience.
